alifornia's Business, Transportation and Housing Agency. In 1993, she was appointed by President Clinton to serve as associate director of the Peace Corps and in 1998 as deputy administrator in the Department of Agriculture, Foreign Agricultural Service. They live in [[Walnut Grove, California|Walnut Grove]] and have six children and nine grandchildren.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.votesmart.org/bio.php?can_id=29664 |title=Representative John Garamendi (CA) |author= |date= |work=[[Project Vote Smart]] |publisher= |accessdate=November 21, 2010}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of Hispanic and Latino Americans in the United States Congress]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category}}\n* [https://garamendi.house.gov/ Congressman John Garamendi] official U.S. House site\n* [http://www.garamendi.org/ John Garamendi for Congress]\n* {{Dmoz|Regional/North_America/United_States/California/Government/Federal/US_House_of_Representatives/John_Garamendi_%5BD-03%5D}}\n* {{CongLinks | congbio=G000559 | votesmart=29664 | fec=H0CA10149 | congress=john-garamendi/G000559 }}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-par|us-ca-hs}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[William T. Bagley|William Bagley]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Member of the [[California State Assembly|California Assembly]]<br>from the [[California's 7th State Assembly district|7th]] district|years=1974\u20131976}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Norman S. Waters|Norman Waters]]}}\n|-\n{{s-par|us-ca-sen}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Al Alquist]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Member of the [[California State Senate|California Senate]]<br>from the [[California's 13th State Senate district|13th]] district|years=1976\u20131984}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Al Alquist]]}}\n|-\n{{s-bef|before=[[Milton Marks]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Member of the [[California State Senate|California Senate]]<br>from the [[California's 5th State Senate district|5th]] district|years=1984\u20131990}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Patrick Johnston (American politician)|Patrick Johnston]]}}\n|-\n{{s-off}}\n{{s-new|r